# Test-Driven Development (TDD) — Core Philosophy

## 1. Core Principle
All production code must originate from tests.

- Tests define behavior before implementation
- No production code is valid unless required by a failing test

---

## 2. TDD Cycle (Invariant)

TDD must follow this strict sequence:

### RED
- Write exactly one failing test
- Test must describe a single behavior
- No production code allowed

### GREEN
- Implement the minimal code required to pass the test
- Do not introduce additional behavior

### REFACTOR
- Improve structure without changing behavior
- All tests must remain passing
- Tests must not be modified

---

## 3. Cycle Constraints
- One cycle = one behavior
- One behavior = one test
- No mixing multiple behaviors
- No skipping or combining phases

---

## 4. Behavior Rule
A valid test must:
- describe observable behavior
- avoid implementation details
- remain valid after refactoring

---

## 5. Refactor Safety Rule
Refactoring is valid only if:
- behavior remains unchanged
- tests remain unchanged
- all tests continue passing